CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F303A1779152634
OL,3,CMSPs to elect new first minister after
OL,4,CScottish elections
OL,6,FMr Swinney told voters during the
OL,7,Felection campaign that a pro-
OL,8,Findependence majority of SNP MSPs
OL,9,Fwould be a mandate. Having failed at
OL,10,Fthat, the first minister has insisted
OL,11,Fthe pro-independence majority the
OL,12,Fparty has along with the Greens still
OL,13,Fcounts as a mandate.
OL,15,FMs Mackay said: "It is welcome that,
OL,16,Fnow the election is over, the SNP
OL,17,Fappears to recognise that Green votes
OL,18,Fare also independence votes. But
OL,19,Frecognition is not enough.
OL,26,@wD@QOU
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G5/10
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNat News CNat TV FClean Feed
FL,304,300,200,140,000,100
PN,30306
SC,0006
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F303A1779152634
OL,3,CMSPs to elect new first minister after
OL,4,CScottish elections
OL,6,F"The First Minister must follow
OL,7,Fthrough on his promise and offer the
OL,8,Fclear roadmap to independence that
OL,9,FScotland deserves and voted for."
OL,11,FThe Scottish Conservatives urged Mr
OL,12,FSwinney to show some "common sense"
OL,13,Fand rule out another deal with the
OL,14,F"anti-oil and gas" Greens.
OL,16,FRussell Findlay, the party's leader,
OL,17,Fclaimed the SNP's "anti-oil and gas
OL,18,Fagenda" would harden if he "ends up at
OL,19,Fthe mercy of the Greens".
OL,26,@nD@AOUqD@aO]tD@VOUtD@cO]vD@AOUvD@RO]yD@
OL,26,ASOUzD@GO]zD@\OU{D@XO]
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G6/10
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNat News CNat TV FClean Feed
FL,304,300,200,140,000,100
PN,30307
SC,0007
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F303A1779152634
OL,3,CMSPs to elect new first minister after
OL,4,CScottish elections
OL,6,FMr Findlay, speaking ahead of the
OL,7,FAberdeen South by-election, said that
OL,8,Fwhile the SNP leader "likes to
OL,9,Fpretend" he supports Scotland's oil
OL,10,Fand gas sector, his party maintains a
OL,11,Fpresumption against new drilling in
OL,12,Fthe North Sea.
OL,14,FHe said: "There are significant
OL,15,Fconcerns that the SNP's anti-oil-and-
OL,16,Fgas agenda will harden if Swinney ends
OL,17,Fup at the mercy of the Greens, who he
OL,18,Fpreviously brought into government and
OL,19,Fwho would turn off the taps overnight.
OL,26,@pD@VOUqD@HO]vD@JOU
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G7/10
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNat News CNat TV FClean Feed
FL,304,300,200,140,000,100
PN,30308
SC,0008
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F303A1779152634
OL,3,CMSPs to elect new first minister after
OL,4,CScottish elections
OL,6,F"It would be basic common sense for
OL,7,F(Mr) Swinney to explicitly rule out
OL,8,Fany form of new coalition or pact
OL,9,Fbetween the SNP and Greens ahead of
OL,10,Fparliament voting to confirm who
OL,11,Fbecomes first minister."
OL,13,FSpeaking to the Press Association on
OL,14,FTuesday, the First Minister said he
OL,15,Fwas confident he could lead the SNP
OL,16,Finto a fifth consecutive term in
OL,17,Fgovernment.
OL,19,FHe said: "The people of Scotland were
OL,20,Fcrystal clear in the election ` they
OL,21,Fwant the SNP to lead the Government.
OL,26,@nD@AOUsD@XO]{D@JOU
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G8/10
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNat News CNat TV FClean Feed
FL,304,300,200,140,000,100
PN,30309
SC,0009
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F303A1779152634
OL,3,CMSPs to elect new first minister after
OL,4,CScottish elections
OL,6,F"We were elected with 58 members of
OL,7,Fthe Scottish Parliament, we've got a
OL,8,Fcommanding lead over the other
OL,9,Fparties, and I look forward to putting
OL,10,Fforward my candidacy to be first
OL,11,Fminister tomorrow and to take forward
OL,12,Fa government that will serve the
OL,13,Fpeople of Scotland."
OL,15,FHe added: "I'm confident that I can
OL,16,Fwin the vote tomorrow and to make sure
OL,17,Fthat I continue to lead a government
OL,18,Fthat will deliver for the people of
OL,19,FScotland."
OL,26,@nD@AOUuD@TO]wD@KOU{D@JO]
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G9/10
